[I] A simple MPEG and AC3 player for Linux, BSD, and Windows systems

[T] MPEG Audio/Video Player is a simple MPEG and AC3 player for Linux, BSD,
[T] and Windows systems. It plays MPEG transport, program, and elementary
[T] stream files. It also has basic DVD support (using libdvdnav on Linux/BSD
[T] systems only). It features newly developed integer decoders for MPEG
[T] 1 & 2 video, MPEG layer 2 audio, and AC3 audio. It includes a
[T] partially working WMV/VC1 decoder capable of displaying I and P frames.

